data.name: Cafe Prato - Four Seasons
data.description: Featuring traditional Italian and Indian cuisines with a Mediterranean twist, Café Prato at Four Seasons Mumbai provides a menu for any occasion.

data.name: HRC
data.description: Hard Rock Cafe Inc. is a chain of theme restaurants founded in 1971 by Isaac Tigrett and Peter Morton in London. In 1979, the cafe began covering its walls with rock and roll memorabilia, a tradition which expanded to others in the chain.

data.name: FLYP Caf'ye 3
data.description: FLYP cafe is India's one of its kind cafe that brings together elements of F&B,retail, entertainment, work culture, creativity and community of like minded people under one versatile and dynamic space that promotes contemporary youth culture.

data.name: 24/7 Restaurant - The Lalit Mumbai
data.description: This round-the-clock multicuisine space is one of infinite possibilities. Frequented for the lavish lunch and dinner buffet spreads, they have speciality stations showcasing everything from Indian chaat to handcrafted desserts.

data.name: Bestseller
data.description: BESTSELLER is an international, family-owned fashion company with a strong foundation. With a range of more than 20 individual fashion brands, BESTSELLER provides fashion clothing and accessories for both women, men, teenagers and children.

data.name: J W Cafe
data.description: This classy contemporary all-day dining restaurant offers all-day dining, featuring delectable Indian and international fare. Start your morning in Mumbai with our hearty breakfast buffet, and be sure to join us for our wonderful Sunday brunch!

data.name: Ziya - The Oberoi Mumbai
data.description: Treat yourself to contemporary Indian flavours and free flowing spirits, every Sunday, with Ziya’s flavorsome Zzz…unday menu at The Oberoi, Mumbai. The exciting restaurant, helmed by twice Michelin-starred Chef Vineet Bhatia, serves ‘evolved’ Indian cuisine to a discerning clientele. Enjoy the indulgence of Sundays in a new style at Ziya.

data.name: Lord Of The Drinks
data.description: A cavernous space under a twinkling canopy of edison bulbs, Lord Of The Drinks in Kamala Mills is sure to take your breath away. It has a vintage air with monochrome striped walls and rich leather sofas, but the menus are undoubtedly modern with creative twists on familiar favourites. With 1,700 square feet at their disposal, it’s a luxurious, spacious experience, the like of which is rarely seen in Mumbai. The highlight of the room is undoubtedly the 200 feet island bar, from which emerge a bevy of innovative cocktails.
